{
  "article_id": "Robinson1891",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "MANY friends and acquaintances, having frequently suggested and urged a republication of the foregoing narrative, on the ground of its being no longer in print, and almost entirely unknown to the reading community of the present day,"
      },
      {
        "text": "the author",
        "entity_key": "arob",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "has been induced to comply with their wishes in an appendix form, by giving a brief statement of events which have transpired since that period when"
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "entity_key": "re_independentca",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "was an independent government, though not recognized as such by"
      },
      {
        "text": "Mexico",
        "entity_key": "gov_mexico",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "[...]"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The three islands,",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Cruz",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scruz",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ",",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Rosa",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sr",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "St. Nicholas",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", lying south of",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Coast Range",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_coastrange",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "of",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", were once populated, and by",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a race",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "apparently of a higher order than that of the Indians on the mainland, as indicated by the many peculiar relics which came to light after their abandonment of",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and their homes, which took place in the early part of the present century.",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The islands",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "were made attractive and important from the vast numbers of fur-seals and sea-otters found there, which naturally called the attention of",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Russian Codiacks",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "rfurcompany",
          "iba",
          "natam_kodiak",
          "1814huntingparty"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of the north, who almost entirely engrossed that species of traffic throughout the whole extent of",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Pacific Coast",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_paccoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "from",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "their possessions in the north",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_russam",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "down to",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this region",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_local",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which they frequently visited; and on one occasion, in a quarrel with",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the islanders",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "at",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "St. Nicholas",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", they inhumanly massacred nearly the whole of the male inhabitants, which act naturally induced",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the entire population of these islands",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "to seek refuge and protection among",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the several missionary establishments on the mainland",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "mi_mainlandmissions",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          13,
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "After the lapse of half a century",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a party of hunters",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "1835crew",
          "chu",
          "isp",
          "iwi",
          "jsjo",
          "jdy",
          "lbu",
          "natam_hawaiian",
          "nativeamericans"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", headed by",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Isaac Williams",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "iwi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", of",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_la",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", embarked in",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a small vessel",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "at",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "for a trip among",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", for the purpose of amusement as well as profit, in the hunting of sea-otter; and reaching",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "St. Nicholas",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "they disembarked, where strolling around over the rocks on the seashore, much to their surprise, they descried",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a group of persons",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "lw",
          "bhagroup"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", evidently endeavoring to escape observation, to whom they gave chase, and soon came up with. They proved to be",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "an aged veteran",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "bha",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "three females",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "lw",
          "bhagroup"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who, by friendly signs, were induced to accompany them to their launch.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "As they proceeded"
      },
      {
        "text": "the elder woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "escaped, darting off amongst the brush-wood, and was soon out of sight; so they continued their way to the launch, where they embarked, leaving"
      },
      {
        "text": "the poor runaway",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "alone on"
      },
      {
        "text": "the deserted isle",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". With a favorable wind, they reached"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "the next day, and proceeded immediately to"
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles",
        "entity_key": "ci_la",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where they arrived and entertained their"
      },
      {
        "text": "rude visitors",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", much to their satisfaction, day after day adding to their comfort and enjoyment, every one in"
      },
      {
        "text": "the town",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "seeming inclined to extend them hospitality."
      },
      {
        "text": "It was not long, however, before they began to realize their change of habit and diet, which finally ended in the death of",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the women",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The old veteran",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "bha",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", bowed down with grief, wandering about from house to house, was at last missed from among the community, and it was not until the expiration of several weeks that he was found at",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where he remained for quite a period, daily seated on the cliffs, gazing, as it were, to catch a glimpse of",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "his island home",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Unhappily, one day his body was seen floating upon the water, crowned with sea-birds. It was taken ashore and buried on",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a little island",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_dmi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", near the entrance of",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the harbor",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_spharbor",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", now called \"",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Dead Man's Isle",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_dmi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ".\" It was supposed that he fell asleep, and while dreaming, perhaps, of",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "his beloved isle",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "his departed companions",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", he fell among the rocks below and died. Such was the end of",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "poor Black Hawk",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "bha",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "!",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Some eighteen years had passed away, until finally an excursion from"
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to"
      },
      {
        "text": "St. Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", headed by"
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. George Nidevah",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", landed there, and during their stay on"
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "they accidentally fell in with"
      },
      {
        "text": "the poor lonely creature",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", so long the sole resident of"
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      },
      {
        "text": "She was taken to",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where she was treated kindly and entertained at the",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "house of Mr. Nidevah",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "nideverhouse",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "; but, like",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her two companions",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", unable to endure the change, she soon fell sick and died,",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the last remaining one of her race",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "During the first few days of her visit in"
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", all available means were made use of to ascertain, if possible, her history and connection with"
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", for which purpose many of"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_missionindians",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "from"
      },
      {
        "text": "the neighboring missions",
        "entity_key": "mi_mainlandmissions",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "were invited to an interview, that ended unsatisfactorily, inasmuch as her language was entirely unintelligible to them, as was theirs to her. The same measures, with the same result, were taken at"
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles",
        "entity_key": "ci_la",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "in regard to"
      },
      {
        "text": "her three companions",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who, like her, had departed unmourned, unhonored, and unknown. Requiescat in pace!"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "[...]"
      }
    ]
  ]
}